017package org.tribuo.impl;
018
019import org.tribuo.Example;
020import org.tribuo.Feature;
021import org.tribuo.FeatureMap;
022import org.tribuo.Output;
023import org.tribuo.VariableInfo;
024import org.tribuo.transform.Transformer;
025import org.tribuo.transform.TransformerMap;
026import org.tribuo.util.Merger;
027
028import java.io.Serializable;
029import java.util.ArrayList;
030import java.util.Collection;
031import java.util.Collections;
032import java.util.HashSet;
033import java.util.Iterator;
034import java.util.List;
035import java.util.Map;
036import java.util.Objects;
037import java.util.Set;
038import java.util.logging.Logger;
039
040/**
041 * This class will not be performant until value types are available in Java. Prefer {@link ArrayExample}.
042 * <p>
043 * An example that's a simple list of features. It is not guaranteed that feature instances are preserved.
044 * @param <T> the type of the features in this example.
045 */
046public class ListExample<T extends Output<T>> extends Example<T> implements Serializable {
047    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(ListExample.class.getName());
048    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;
049
050    private final List<Feature> features = new ArrayList<>();
051
052    public ListExample(T output, float weight) {
053        super(output,weight);
054    }
055     
056    public ListExample(T output) {
057        super(output);
058    }
059
060    public ListExample(Example<T> other) {
061        super(other);
062        for (Feature f : other) {
063            addWithoutSort(f.clone());
064        }
065        sort();
066    }
067
068    public ListExample(T output, List<? extends Feature> features) {
069        super(output);
070        for (Feature f : features) {
071            addWithoutSort(f.clone());
072        }
073        sort();
074    }
075
076    public ListExample(T output, String[] featureNames, double[] featureValues) {
077        super(output);
078        if (featureNames.length != featureValues.length) {
079            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Supplied names have length " + featureNames.length + ", supplied values have length " + featureValues.length);
080        }
081        for (int i = 0; i < featureNames.length; i++) {
082            addWithoutSort(new Feature(featureNames[i],featureValues[i]));
083        }
084        sort();
085    }
086
087    /**
088     * Adds a feature without sorting the feature list. Used in the mass add methods and constructors.
089     * @param feature The feature to add.
090     */
091    private void addWithoutSort(Feature feature) {
092        features.add(feature);
093    }
094
095    @Override
096    public void add(Feature feature) {
097        addWithoutSort(feature);
098        sort();
099    }
100
101    @Override
102    public void addAll(Collection<? extends Feature> features) {
103        this.features.addAll(features);
104        sort();
105    }
106    
107    public void clear() {
108        features.clear();
109    }
110    
111    @Override
112    public int size() {
113        return features.size();
114    }
115
116    @Override
117    public ListExample<T> copy() {
118        return new ListExample<>(this);
119    }
120
121    @Override
122    public Iterator<Feature> iterator() {
123        return features.iterator();
124    }
125    
126    @Override
127    public String toString() {
128        StringBuilder builder = new StringBuilder();
129
130        builder.append("ListExample(numFeatures=");
131        builder.append(features.size());
132        builder.append(",output=");
133        builder.append(output);
134        builder.append(",weight=");
135        builder.append(weight);
136        if (metadata != null) {
137            builder.append(",metadata=");
138            builder.append(metadata.toString());
139        }
140        builder.append(",features=");
141        builder.append(features.toString());
142        builder.append(")");
143
144        return builder.toString();
145    }
146
147    /**
148     * Sorts the feature list to maintain the lexicographic order invariant.
149     */
150    @Override
151    protected void sort() {
152        features.sort(Feature.featureNameComparator());
153    }
154
155    @Override
156    public void removeFeatures(List<Feature> featureList) {
157        features.removeAll(featureList);
158    }
159
160    @Override
161    public void reduceByName(Merger merger) {
162        if (features.size() > 0) {
163            List<Feature> featuresToRemove = new ArrayList<>();
164            int buffer = 0;
165            String name = features.get(buffer).getName();
166            for (int i = 1; i < features.size(); i++) {
167                Feature f = features.get(i);
168                if (f.getName().equals(name)) {
169                    // Found repeated name, add to removal list and merge into the original value.
170                    featuresToRemove.add(f);
171                    Feature old = features.remove(buffer);
172                    features.add(buffer,new Feature(old.getName(),merger.merge(old.getValue(),f.getValue())));
173                } else {
174                    // Found new name, update buffer and carry on.
175                    name = f.getName();
176                    buffer = i;
177                }
178            }
179            features.removeAll(featuresToRemove);
180        } else {
181            logger.finer("Reducing an example with no features.");
182        }
183    }
184
185    @Override
186    public Feature lookup(String i) {
187        int index = Collections.binarySearch(features,new Feature(i,1.0));
188        if (index < 0) {
189            return null;
190        } else {
191            return features.get(index);
192        }
193    }
194
195    @Override
196    public void set(Feature feature) {
197        int index = Collections.binarySearch(features,feature);
198        if (index < 0) {
199            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Feature " + feature + " not found in example.");
200        } else {
201            features.set(index,feature);
202        }
203    }
204
205    @Override
206    public boolean validateExample() {
207        if (features.isEmpty()) {
208            return false;
209        } else {
210            Set<String> names = new HashSet<>();
211            for (Feature f : features) {
212                names.add(f.getName());
213                if (Double.isNaN(f.getValue())) {
214                    return false;
215                }
216            }
217            return names.size() == features.size();
218        }
219    }
220
221    @Override
222    public void transform(TransformerMap transformerMap) {
223        for (Map.Entry<String,List<Transformer>> e : transformerMap.entrySet()) {
224            int index = Collections.binarySearch(features, new Feature(e.getKey(),1.0));
225            if (index >= 0) {
226                double value = features.get(index).getValue();
227                for (Transformer t : e.getValue()) {
228                    value = t.transform(value);
229                }
230                features.set(index,new Feature(e.getKey(),value));
231            }
232        }
233    }
234
235    @Override
236    protected void densify(List<String> featureList) {
237        int oldSize = features.size();
238        int curPos = 0;
239        for (String curName : featureList) {
240            // If we've reached the end of our old feature set, just insert.
241            if (curPos == oldSize) {
242                features.add(new Feature(curName,0.0));
243            } else {
244                // Check to see if our insertion candidate is the same as the current feature name.
245                int comparison = curName.compareTo(features.get(curPos).getName());
246                if (comparison < 0) {
247                    // If it's earlier, insert it.
248                    features.add(new Feature(curName,0.0));
249                } else if (comparison == 0) {
250                    // Otherwise just bump our pointer, we've already got this feature.
251                    curPos++;
252                }
253            }
254        }
255        // Sort the features
256        sort();
257    }
258
259    @Override
260    public void canonicalize(FeatureMap featureMap) {
261        List<Feature> remadeFeatures = new ArrayList<>();
262        for(Feature f: features) {
263            VariableInfo vi = featureMap.get(f.getName());
264            if(vi != null) {
265                remadeFeatures.add(new Feature(vi.getName(), f.getValue()));
266            } else {
267                remadeFeatures.add(f);
268            }
269        }
270        features.clear();
271        features.addAll(remadeFeatures);
272    }
273
274    @Override
275    public boolean equals(Object o) {
276        if (this == o) return true;
277        if (!(o instanceof ListExample)) return false;
278        ListExample<?> that = (ListExample<?>) o;
279        if (Objects.equals(metadata,that.metadata) && output.getClass().equals(that.output.getClass())) {
280            @SuppressWarnings("unchecked") //guarded by a getClass.
281            boolean outputTest = output.fullEquals((T) that.output);
282            return outputTest && features.equals(that.features);
283        } else {
284            return false;
285        }
286    }
287
288    @Override
289    public int hashCode() {
290        return Objects.hash(features);
291    }
292}
